---
---

<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Ockham — Intelligence Infrastructure</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;700&family=Source+Serif+4:ital,opsz,wght@0,8..60,300;0,8..60,400;0,8..60,600;0,8..60,700;1,8..60,300;1,8..60,400&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  :root {
    --bg: #0a0a0a;
    --fg: #e8e4df;
    --dim: #706b63;
    --accent: #c4792c;
    --accent-glow: #c4792c22;
    --code-bg: #0e0d0b;
    --border: #2a2622;
    --border-light: #332e28;
    --tag-bg: #1a1714;
    --surface: #121110;
    --green: #8a9a7b;
  }

  * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }

  body {
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--fg);
    font-family: 'Source Serif 4', Georgia, serif;
    line-height: 1.7;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  }

  body::before {
    content: '';
    position: fixed;
    inset: 0;
    background-image: url("data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg viewBox='0 0 256 256' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cfilter id='n'%3E%3CfeTurbulence type='fractalNoise' baseFrequency='0.9' numOctaves='4' stitchTiles='stitch'/%3E%3C/filter%3E%3Crect width='100%25' height='100%25' filter='url(%23n)' opacity='0.03'/%3E%3C/svg%3E");
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 999;
  }

  .page {
    max-width: 740px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 72px 24px 140px;
  }

  .hero { margin-bottom: 72px; }

  .hero h1 {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 52px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -2px;
    color: var(--fg);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }

  .hero-tag {
    font-family: 'Source Serif 4', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 25px;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.35;
    color: #979089;
    max-width: none;
  }

  .hero-tag-strong {
    color: var(--fg);
  }

  .hero-subhead {
    font-size: 21px;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--dim);
    max-width: 42rem;
    margin-top: 18px;
  }

  .rule {
    width: 48px;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--accent);
    margin: 56px 0;
    opacity: 0.5;
  }

  .s { margin-bottom: 56px; }

  .s-label {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 2.5px;
    color: var(--dim);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .s p {
    font-size: 17px;
    color: var(--fg);
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.85;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .s p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .s p strong { font-weight: 600; }
  .s p em { color: var(--accent); font-style: italic; }

  .thesis {
    border-left: 2px solid var(--accent);
    padding: 24px 0 24px 28px;
    margin: 56px 0;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--accent-glow) 0%, transparent 50%);
  }

  .thesis p {
    font-size: 19px;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: var(--fg);
  }

  .thesis strong { font-weight: 700; }

  .stack {
    margin: 36px 0 16px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .stack-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 120px 1fr;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    transition: background 0.15s;
  }

  .stack-row:hover { background: var(--surface); }

  .stack-name {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--accent);
    padding: 16px 16px 16px 0;
    border-right: 1px solid var(--border);
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
  }

  .stack-text {
    padding: 16px 0 16px 20px;
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--fg);
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .stack-text .ghost {
    color: var(--dim);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  @media (max-width: 540px) {
    .stack-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .stack-name { border-right: none; padding: 12px 0 0; font-size: 13px; }
    .stack-text { padding: 4px 0 12px; font-size: 14px; }
  }

  .dual {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 32px;
    margin: 36px 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 540px) { .dual { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 20px; } }

  .dual-col h3 {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }

  .dual-col.y h3 { color: var(--accent); }
  .dual-col.n h3 { color: var(--dim); }
  .dual-col ul { list-style: none; }

  .dual-col ul li {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 13px;
    padding: 5px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .dual-col.y ul li { color: var(--fg); }
  .dual-col.n ul li {
    color: var(--dim);
    text-decoration: line-through;
    text-decoration-color: var(--border);
  }

  .callout {
    background: var(--code-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 3px;
    padding: 22px 26px;
    margin: 28px 0;
  }

  .callout p {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--dim);
    line-height: 1.75;
    font-weight: 300;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .callout code {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .inline-link {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
    transition: border-color 0.15s;
  }

  .inline-link:visited {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .inline-link:hover {
    border-bottom-color: var(--accent);
  }

  .status {
    margin: 36px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .status-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 120px 1fr 80px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 8px 0;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .status-name {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--fg);
  }

  .status-what {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--dim);
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  .status-badge {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    text-align: right;
  }

  .status-badge.live { color: var(--green); }
  .status-badge.wip { color: var(--accent); }

  @media (max-width: 540px) {
    .status-row { grid-template-columns: 100px 1fr 60px; }
    .status-what { font-size: 12px; }
  }

  .tags {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 8px;
    margin: 14px 0;
  }

  .tag {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--dim);
    background: var(--tag-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 3px 11px;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  .foot {
    margin-top: 96px;
    padding-top: 40px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .foot-latin {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--dim);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  .foot-who {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--border-light);
    margin-top: 6px;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .foot-end {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--border-light);
    margin-top: 28px;
    letter-spacing: 0.3px;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="page">

  <header class="hero">
    <h1>ockham</h1>
    <div class="hero-tag">Control planes for AI workflows. <span class="hero-tag-strong">No ghosts. Just machines.</span></div>
    <div class="hero-subhead">Replay + regression testing for production AI workflows.</div>
  </header>

  <div class="rule"></div>

  <section class="s">
    <div class="s-label">The Problem</div>
    <p>
      Most AI infrastructure still asks teams to think in <em>ghosts</em>.
    </p>
    <p>
      When workflows are framed as personalities with memory, judgment, and collaboration,
      teams stop designing around explicit state, control flow, validation, and reproducible
      behavior. The system becomes harder to test, harder to compare, and harder to change safely.
      Control surfaces get fuzzier. Small prompt changes affect too much at once. Evals drift
      toward vibes. Debugging becomes interpretation instead of procedure.
    </p>
    <p>
      The result is familiar: brittle workflows, silent regressions, manual QA, and production
      changes that feel riskier than they should.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="thesis">
    <p>
      Ockham is built on a simple rule: <strong style="color: var(--accent)">don't replace systems engineering with ghost stories.</strong>
      Treat AI workflows as systems to control, test, replay, and verify, not personalities to coax,
      interpret, and hope behave.
    </p>
  </div>

  <section class="s">
    <div class="s-label">The Machine, Not the Ghost</div>

    <div class="dual">
      <div class="dual-col y">
        <h3>What we build</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Replay + regression for AI workflows</li>
          <li>Explicit state, routing, validation</li>
          <li>Workflow verification</li>
          <li>Reproducible debugging</li>
          <li>Evidence from real runs</li>
          <li>Safer production changes</li>
          <li>Control surfaces you can reason about</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="dual-col n">
        <h3>What we don't</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Persona-driven orchestration</li>
          <li>Hidden state as architecture</li>
          <li>Inter-agent mythology</li>
          <li>Vibes-based verification</li>
          <li>Interpretive debugging</li>
          <li>Rerun-and-hope releases</li>
          <li>Marketecture over control</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="s">
    <div class="s-label">Interoperability</div>
    <p>
      Ockham can work with the protocols without inheriting the ghost story.
    </p>
    <div class="callout">
      <p>
        <code>MCP</code> endpoints are tool nodes. <code>A2A</code> services
        are external nodes with capability-based routing. Agent Cards are
        service descriptors. Tasks are RPC calls with a lifecycle.
        Ockham consumes the protocols. It doesn't buy the ontology.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="s">
    <div class="s-label">Design Lineage</div>
    <p>
      These are not new problems. We inherit from the infrastructure
      that already solves them and do not pretend otherwise.
    </p>
    <div class="tags">
      <span class="tag">Dagster</span>
      <span class="tag">Temporal</span>
      <span class="tag">Ray</span>
      <span class="tag">Petri nets</span>
      <span class="tag">Apache Beam</span>
      <span class="tag">Pregel</span>
      <span class="tag">Erlang/OTP</span>
      <span class="tag">Make / Bazel</span>
    </div>
    <p style="margin-top: 16px;">
      The novel surface is narrow and honest: replayable workflow evidence,
      reusable regression cases from real runs, and safer prompt, model, and
      workflow changes in production. Everything else is borrowed. That's the point.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="s">
    <div class="s-label">Why Rust</div>
    <p>
      Because the orchestration layer shouldn't be the slow part.
      Because strict type systems prevent the category errors we're
      trying to eliminate. Because infrastructure that outlasts hype
      cycles should be built in a language designed to outlast hype cycles.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="s">
    <div class="s-label">Contact</div>
    <p>
      If you're building production AI workflows and want to compare notes,
      reach out at <a class="inline-link" href="mailto:inbox@robertdberry.com">inbox@robertdberry.com</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <footer class="foot">
    <div class="foot-latin">Entia non sunt multiplicanda praeter necessitatem.</div>
    <div class="foot-who">William of Ockham, c. 1287 – 1347</div>
    <div class="foot-end">No ghosts. Just machines.</div>
  </footer>

</div>

</body>
</html>
